org.corpus_tools.peppermodules.flex.readers

Class FLExDocumentReader

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.xml.sax.helpers.DefaultHandler
      • org.xml.sax.ext.DefaultHandler2
        • org.corpus_tools.peppermodules.flex.readers.FLExReader
          • org.corpus_tools.peppermodules.flex.readers.FLExDocumentReader
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    FLExText, ContentHandler, DTDHandler, EntityResolver, ErrorHandler, DeclHandler, EntityResolver2, LexicalHandler

    public class FLExDocumentReader
extends FLExReader
implements FLExText

    This class parses an xml file following the model of FLExText.

    In the process, the FLEx XML values are mapped onto a Salt model following these principles:

    • interlinear-text elements are mapped to SDocuments.
    • paragraphs, are mapped to SSpans, which span over
    • phrases, which are mapped to SSpans, which span over
    • words and morphs, both of which are mapped to STokens, which are tied to an STextualDS each.
    • Annotations (items) for each layer are tied to the respective SNode (SToken or SSpan)
    • XML attributes are mapped as SAnnotation to the respective SNode.
    Author:
    Stephan Druskat mail@sdruskat.net
